  "response": "Here's a comparison of Amazon Prime Video and Netflix in India:\n\nAmazon Prime Video:\n- Lower cost (included with Amazon Prime subscription)\n- More local Indian content and regional language movies\n- Includes free shipping and other Amazon Prime benefits\n- Allows offline downloads\n- Some content is free, some requires additional rental/purchase\n- Includes original Indian web series\n\nNetflix:\n- Higher subscription cost\n- More international and global content\n- More Netflix original series and movies\n- Higher quality original content\n- Better recommendation algorithm\n- More consistent streaming quality\n- No additional benefits beyond streaming\n\nSimilarities:\n- Both offer streaming on multiple devices\n- Both have mobile-friendly apps\n- Both produce original content\n- Both offer HD and 4K streaming options\n\nPricing (approximate):\n- Amazon Prime: \u20b91,499/year\n- Netflix: Basic - \u20b9199/month, Standard - \u20b9499/month, Premium - \u20b9649/month\n\nOverall, Amazon Prime Video offers better value for money, while Netflix provides a more premium content experience. The choice depends on individual preferences, budget, and desired content.",
